   "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
   "body" : "When the `debug.log` file reaches a certain size (default, 1MB), rename it\r\nto a similar name that includes the current time, and truncate\r\n`debug.log`. Keep a limited number of rotated files (default 10). This\r\nprovides a sliding window of debug messages so that disk space isn't\r\nconsumed without limit (until `bitcoind` restarts). This is similar to\r\nUnix `logrotate(8)` but requires no external tools and complex\r\nconfiguration, is enabled by default, and should work on Windows.\r\n\r\nThe names are constructed so that they sort in time-order;\r\n`cat debug*.log` will give all available log lines in the correct order.",
